args:
Felicia's hometown has been laid to waste by
Thanatos, who was not truly defeated earlier.
The fiend then attempts to take Phantom's life
right in front of her. Seeking to end the chain
of tragedies for good and all, the party takes
up their weapons and heads into battle.
We should be at my village once we pass\nthrough this forest.
Heh. You look so happy, Felicia.
It's great to finally be heading home!
Beg pardon, but might I make a request\nof you, {player_name}?
Would you and your comrades escort\nFelicia the rest of the way?
This is where Felicia and I part ways.\nI will not be going to the village.
Wait, but you were the one who WANTED\nto escort her back to her village.
Now that she has you and Thanatos is\ngone, my presence is no longer required.
Further, if I go along to the village,\nits people will be...frightened of me.
See me, Felicia! Behold my hideous form!\nWhile you may have grown used to it,\nit sets others quaking in fear!
...Try bringing a dragon such as that\nback to your village.
I'll just explain to them what a\nkind and gentle creature you are.
You're not scary, and you AREN'T hideous!\nI'm sure they'll all understand.
Sylvans are weak creatures who will be\nunable to look past my appearance.
Phantom... Are you really doing this?
Our parting was decided from the moment\nwe met. We're merely moving it ahead.
Yes, Flamewyrm—and I have no regrets.\nAll will be well now.
Fare you well, Felicia.\nMay you live in happiness.
Phantom, wait! I still want to—
No. We're going. If we don't get you home,\neverything he did will be for nothing.
If you are happy...then all is well.
Ah, but parting IS such sweet sorrow!
Huh? Wh-what's going on?\nIt can't be...
No... The village has been destroyed!
Father! Mother! Everyone!\nIt's me, Felicia! I've come back!
Did I not say you have no home\nto return to?
It's a tear in space! Get ready, everyone!
Did you think you could escape from me,\nmy beloved dancer?
How are you still ALIVE, dude?!\nWe beat you like a carpet!
Fools! I am the king of death!\nI control the very essence of life!
A trifling assault such as yours could\nnever fell me!
Then let me make it clear:\nYou belong to me now.
You need no home other than what\nI can provide.
Thus, after I spirited you away,\nI laid waste to this village.
Our attacks went right through him!
Is this Thanatos some manner of illusion?!
As always, you see the truth too late.\nI await in the space between worlds,\nprepared to usher my dancer to my side.
Be overjoyed, Felicia, for I have made the\ndecor of the stage ever more gorgeous,\nthat it might match your beauty!
I have gone out of my way to grant you\na life of ease. Does this not please you?
There is no reason for you\nto ever leave my side.
This is how great my love for you is.
Now return to me, and let us dance\ntogether in my world of darkness!
No! I'll never come back to you!
Only a demon would steal everything from\nsomeone and claim this to be love.
It seems that interloper has whispered\nmore poison into your ear than I knew.\nWell, his time is ending.
Bring forth that hideous dragon,\nmy servants!
I have captured the dragon who\nswept you away from me.
This hideous beast would do naught\nbut threaten you, my dancer!\nCan you not see this?!
That's not true! Phantom SAVED me!
But perhaps you will see the truth when\nI remove this repulsive beast's head!
The time of execution is at hand!
Whoa! Felicia ran in front of Phantom!
What are you doing, my sweet?\nAre you truly protecting this...thing?
I won't let you take his life...\nI won't let you take ANY more lives!
I'm done running, Phantom.\nI'm going to protect you!
He stole my family and my home—\nI won't let him steal you as well!
If you're going to kill Phantom,\nyou'll have to kill me first!
WHY WILL YOU NOT GRANT ME THE FAVOR\nOF YOUR ATTENTIONS, FELICIA?!
I love you so, yet still you reject me!\nWhy do you force me to be alone?!
Because you think of nothing but yourself!
Lies! I think only of my Felicia! I...
Ah, I see it now. It simply won't do for\nyou to have someone else love you.
In that case, there is but one way forward:\nI must reap the souls of all gathered here!
This ends here, Thanatos. We won't let you\nkeep stealing lives to feed your desires.
To live is to be free, and what you seek\nto do here is no life at all.
No, dancer! Look at me! Look ONLY at me!\nSpare your gaze for my visage alone!
Servants! Take the dancer away!\nKill any who would interfere!
We're gonna take your warped love\nand bash it into shape!
This time, we defeat you for good!
